               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Kifayat al-Atibba by Abu Ji? (Abu Hayy?) b. Husam al-din TY*Y? (BTYNY?).
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Ellis_Persian_14-item1">
                     <author key="person_f101">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied">Abu Ji? (Abu Hayy?) b. Husam al-din TY*Y? (BTYNY?).</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_9684">Kifayat al-Atibba.</title>
                     <note>F1a. Partly effaced impression of a large round Persian seal, probably seventeenth or eighteenth century beside a largely effaced note concerning the book. Leaf attached before f1, recto: a) medical prescriptions. b) Note of possession in red naskh above two faint impressions in red of the seal of Muhammad Taqi, dated A.H. 1266, as on 511(525)b. Folios now loose; kept tied between two pieces of English cardboard. Some notes by Ellis on used envelopes and a paper with a prayer and a charm in Arabic and Persian are included. A comprehensive medical work in twenty books, stated in the preface to include translations from Indian works. The main text is preceded by a table of contents. Headings and ruled margins in red.</note>
                     <incipit>Amma ba'd in kitabist musamma bi-kifayat al-atibba</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Storey, ii, p. 321. Evidently the work is uncommon.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
